7 Section 1. R.S. 11:185(D)(3) is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
8 §185. Educational requirements for members of retirement system boards of trustees
9 * * *
10 D.(1) * * *
11 (3) Each year, any member to whom this Section applies shall attend at least
12 eight seven hours of investment training, four two hours of actuarial science
13 information education, two hours one hour of education regarding the laws, rules,
14 and regulations applicable to his system, and two hours of instruction on fiduciary
15 duty and ethics. These training hours may be conducted by the staff of the respective
16 retirement systems or by outside experts. Two or more systems may combine any
17 such training. Any member who is elected or appointed to the board for the first time
18 on or after June first shall be required to comply only with the provisions of
19 Paragraph (4) of this Subsection.
